22:46.297 --> 22:49.662
I want to go out and share the gospel of Jesus Christ with everybody.

22:50.743 --> 22:52.626
I know I'm supposed to do that.

22:52.994 --> 22:54.636
It's God's job to sort them out.

22:54.736 --> 22:58.019
Remember, I told you that we're in sales, not management, right?

23:00.401 --> 23:02.543
Who is saved as a management question?

23:03.024 --> 23:05.806
Telling people how to be saved is a sales question.

23:05.846 --> 23:09.930
Well, I'm in sales, not management.

23:09.950 --> 23:21.081
And so this is what in this, this Esau I have hated here is a Hebrew idiom that's meant to draw a very clear distinction.

23:21.161 --> 23:22.482
It does not mean

23:22.722 --> 23:26.788
It does not carry the connotation of God hated Esau.

23:27.509 --> 23:33.657
It's simply an idiom that she used to make a very stark contrast between the two.

23:33.697 --> 23:38.504
And so God reminds them, I have chosen you as my people.

23:40.006 --> 23:48.978
Someone has said, Israel needed to consider what her lot would have been if she, like Edom, had not been elected to a covenant relationship with God.

23:49.314 --> 24:03.031
Both Israel and Edom received judgment from God at the hands of the Babylonians, yet God repeatedly promised to restore Israel, because they were holy righteous and did everything that God wanted to do?

24:03.051 --> 24:07.617
No, because he's God, and he keeps his promises.

24:09.539 --> 24:13.464
But he condemned Edom to complete destruction never to be restored.

24:14.866 --> 24:18.130
The Edomites, you can't go to the country of Edom today.

24:19.458 --> 24:35.514
The last really influential Edomite was eventually in the New Testament, they became known as the Edumians, and Herod the Great was the last influential Edomite, and we last saw him when he tried to have all the babies, all the male babies massacred.

24:36.655 --> 24:43.521
And after his death, the Edomites kind of fade away into history, almost never to be seen or heard from again.

24:43.601 --> 24:48.466
God wants these people to consider how hopeless they would be

24:48.738 --> 24:50.099
without his great love.

24:51.601 --> 24:53.903
Man, that's something that we ought to consider, isn't it?

24:55.384 --> 25:02.331
I mean, sometimes we ought to consider what would my life be without God's great love?

25:03.612 --> 25:18.226
Because I think that the one thing that every single person on this planet needs, and it doesn't matter if you're in Uganda or Kenya or Ukraine or Russia or here, every person on this planet needs hope.

25:20.162 --> 25:26.168
and hope that's real hope is only found in the gospel of Jesus Christ.

25:28.351 --> 25:35.919
Their hope is in the fact that God loves them and he has promised never to stop loving them.

25:35.999 --> 25:46.610
And my friends, our hope is in the truth that despite myself, God loves me because he has promised to love me.

25:47.010 --> 25:55.361
And because he is faithful and just and true and pure and I am not, then God's, God upholds me.

25:55.381 --> 25:58.506
He loves me because of his great character.

25:58.526 --> 26:16.370
And because God is a God of great character, when I get ready to die and leave this world and I slip the bounds of this place and go to heaven, I know I'm going to get there, not because Lance is a good dude, but because God is merciful, gracious, and he has said he loves me.

26:16.482 --> 26:21.907
And because he cannot lie, then my future is safe, set, and secure.

26:22.888 --> 26:23.769
And so is yours.

26:25.631 --> 26:29.995
One day, the people will recognize the greatness of God and His love for them.

26:33.938 --> 26:46.450
God's great love, it is said... God's great love, it is said...

26:48.770 --> 26:54.018
Oh.

26:54.038 --> 26:58.685
Well.

26:58.705 --> 27:01.349
All right.

27:01.369 --> 27:02.470
John Piper wrote this.

27:02.530 --> 27:06.396
I think it's really great about the recognition of God's love in our life.

27:08.900 --> 27:15.249
God's love, he said, should make us tremble with tears of joy knowing that we belong to this great God.

27:17.513 --> 27:18.354
He said, if we

27:18.466 --> 27:23.512
If we honestly assessed our life, how should it impact our lives?

27:23.592 --> 27:26.095
How should God's great love impact our lives?

27:26.135 --> 27:33.144
And he says this, if we saw the greatness of God's love for us, we wouldn't be so greedy and covetous.

27:35.226 --> 27:41.414
If we saw the greatness of God's love for us, our eyes wouldn't stray after lustful images and thoughts.

27:43.977 --> 27:47.922
If we saw the greatness of God's love for us, we wouldn't get angry at our children.

27:48.226 --> 27:49.007
So easily.

27:52.471 --> 27:58.398
If we saw the greatness of God's love for us, we wouldn't pout and get hurt so easily in our marriages.

27:59.699 --> 28:04.004
If we saw the greatness of God's love for us, we wouldn't worry about our look so much.

28:05.326 --> 28:06.307
I haven't ever done that.

28:06.347 --> 28:06.767
It's weird.

28:11.453 --> 28:16.178
If we saw the greatness of God's love for us, we wouldn't get so discouraged with the evil

28:18.050 --> 28:19.892
and godlessness of our own culture.

28:22.494 --> 28:25.297
God's love can totally transform us.

28:27.840 --> 28:33.926
The next thing that we get from Malachi is we get a message to honor the Lord.

28:35.668 --> 28:41.413
In Malachi chapter one, verses six through 11, it says, a son honors his father and the servant, his master.

28:42.194 --> 28:45.938
If them, if then I am a father, where is my honor?

28:46.754 --> 28:48.857
And if I'm a master, where is my fear?

28:49.599 --> 28:50.861
Says the Lord of hosts to you.

28:51.682 --> 28:56.349
O priest who despised my name, but you say, how have we despised your name?

28:58.313 --> 28:59.995
Again, clueless.

29:01.758 --> 29:11.774
They know exactly what they're doing, but they're still trying to argue, how have we despised your name by offering polluted food upon my altar?

29:12.195 --> 29:14.258
But you say, how have we polluted you?

29:14.914 --> 29:17.558
by saying that the Lord's table may be despised.

29:18.379 --> 29:21.823
When you offer blind animals and sacrifice, is that not evil?

29:22.264 --> 29:25.588
And when you offer those who are lame or sick, is that not evil?

29:26.189 --> 29:27.751
Present that to your governor.

29:28.192 --> 29:30.234
Will he accept you or show you favor?

29:30.735 --> 29:31.857
Says the Lord of hosts.

29:32.998 --> 29:40.148
I mean, throughout this book, there's all these questions and asking questions is not a bad thing, but these questions are defensive questions.

29:40.188 --> 29:41.890
They're defiant questions.

29:41.930 --> 29:44.914
They're like a child who constantly says, why?

29:45.154 --> 29:48.299
when they don't want to do what it is that their mom or dad is asking them to do.

29:48.319 --> 29:49.260
And they just say, why?

29:49.360 --> 29:49.641
Why?

29:49.721 --> 29:50.001
Why?

29:50.102 --> 29:50.402
Why?

29:50.883 --> 29:51.604
All the time.

29:52.245 --> 29:54.508
In verse six, Israel's not honoring God.

29:54.609 --> 29:56.632
That word honor means glory.

29:58.394 --> 30:02.601
God deserves glory and honor.

30:03.983 --> 30:09.872
The Lord says, just like a son honors his father and his servant and his master and a citizen, his governor.

30:10.433 --> 30:11.775
So we are to honor the Lord.

30:12.556 --> 30:13.778
I mean, if your favorite,

30:14.050 --> 30:16.934
I was going to say presidential candidate, but I don't know.

30:16.954 --> 30:18.256
We got to aim higher than that.

30:18.336 --> 30:24.224
If your favorite college football coach came over to your house, right?

30:25.346 --> 30:28.009
I mean, to me, that's more important than the president anyway.

30:28.029 --> 30:36.982
But if your favorite college football coach came over to your house to sit down and have a meal with you, would you whip out the leftovers?

30:38.424 --> 30:38.744
No.

30:39.525 --> 30:41.268
Would you put it on paper plates?

30:42.329 --> 30:42.930
No.

30:43.618 --> 30:46.362
You would set the best table, right?

30:46.422 --> 30:51.470
Whoever it is that you give honor to, you would set the best table, you would honor him.

30:51.530 --> 31:00.744
And here are the priests not honoring God when they said, you know, when they offer these unlawful sacrifices for atonement.

31:01.565 --> 31:12.562
Deuteronomy 15, 21 says, but if it has any blemish, if it is lame or blind or has any serious blemish, whatever, you shall not sacrifice to the Lord your God.

31:13.730 --> 31:20.242
And so the people literally knew that it was not a pure, clean, holy sacrifice.

31:20.262 --> 31:24.350
They knew that it was a cheap, half-hearted way to worship God.

31:26.194 --> 31:28.578
They were basically saying, oh man, you know what?

31:28.679 --> 31:36.754
If we have to do this, let me go out and find the most blemish, worst animal, the cheapest animal,

31:36.962 --> 31:42.952
I can possibly find the one who is going to give me nothing in return and I'll honor that.

31:43.032 --> 31:44.374
I'll honor God with that.

31:47.379 --> 31:53.589
Then he says, God says, and now entreat the favor of God that he may be gracious to us.

31:54.491 --> 31:56.214
Was such a gift from your hand?

31:56.274 --> 31:58.838
Will he show any favor to any of you?

31:59.739 --> 32:00.721
Says the Lord of hosts.

32:01.482 --> 32:03.826
In other words, God is not the cosmic chump.

32:04.770 --> 32:14.019
He knows whether our hearts are bent towards honoring Him and glorifying Him, or whether they are bent toward anything else but that.

32:16.522 --> 32:22.388
Oh, that there were one among you who would shut the doors that you might not kindle fire on my altar in vain.

32:22.408 --> 32:28.614
I have no pleasure in you, says the Lord of hosts, and I will not accept an offering from your hand.

32:29.595 --> 32:32.178
God is saying, I wish somebody had the courage

32:32.290 --> 32:36.555
to just go shut the doors of the temple and not let anybody in.

32:36.575 --> 32:45.847
I would rather them not worship me at all than I had him bring me these kind of lame sacrifices that they're bringing.

32:46.468 --> 32:48.150
That would actually honor me."

32:49.371 --> 32:57.842
In verse 11, he says, from the rising of the sun to its setting, my name will be great among the nations.

32:58.050 --> 33:05.879
And in every place incense will be offered to my name and a pure offering for my name will be great among the nation says the Lord of hosts.

33:07.260 --> 33:09.503
Listen, God will not be mocked.

33:10.684 --> 33:12.326
His name is great.

33:13.667 --> 33:19.614
And God says to them, if you won't honor me, others will, right?

33:20.014 --> 33:23.378
It's a privilege to live your life devoted

33:23.522 --> 33:25.745
to honoring and glorifying God.

33:25.765 --> 33:30.672
It is an absolute privilege and it is the highest call in our lives.

33:33.495 --> 33:36.119
So real quick, what do we learn from this?

33:37.601 --> 33:41.386
Well, the first thing is is that we make a connection to the gospel.

33:43.048 --> 33:48.636
The pure and healthy animal that they had to sacrifice reminds us of the gospel.

33:50.178 --> 33:53.522
God ultimately was the one who was going to provide the unblemished

33:53.698 --> 33:56.682
Lamb, the perfect Holy Son of God.

33:56.722 --> 34:00.447
There is an illusion here to John the Baptist.

34:01.168 --> 34:06.256
John chapter 1 verse 29 says, Behold the Lamb of God who takes away the sin of the world.

34:06.316 --> 34:12.164
This is when John the Baptist sees this unblemished sacrifice and he knows Jesus is the one.

34:12.204 --> 34:13.285
He is the chosen one.

34:13.365 --> 34:14.527
He is the perfect one.

34:16.029 --> 34:17.491
The gospel demands this.

34:18.653 --> 34:22.418
That's why we need Jesus to save us because we are blemished.

34:23.138 --> 34:25.000
We have spiritual flaws.

34:25.140 --> 34:27.683
We're sinners, but Christ is pure.

34:27.743 --> 34:37.935
And so one important application is to rejoice that Christ is the perfect sacrifice because our lives depend on it.

34:39.697 --> 34:42.481
The second thing is we're to honor the Lord wholeheartedly.

34:43.682 --> 34:47.246
We don't honor God with sacrifices of animals anymore.

34:48.027 --> 34:50.450
But Romans chapter 12 verse 1 says,

34:53.026 --> 35:08.026
I appeal to you, therefore, brothers, by the mercies of God to present your bodies as a living sacrifice, holy and acceptable to God, which is your spiritual act of worship."

35:08.046 --> 35:08.226
Right?

35:08.266 --> 35:14.294
God says, listen, bring me your whole body as an act of worship.

35:16.156 --> 35:17.318
And so what is our life?

35:17.438 --> 35:20.562
Well, our life is somewhat of our lives is our time.

35:22.306 --> 35:24.309
You know, we offer God time.

35:24.349 --> 35:29.335
We don't selfishly manage our time only for ourselves.

35:30.577 --> 35:32.920
Even our free time belongs to God.

35:33.801 --> 35:38.968
And God certainly deserves more than the leftover time that we often bring to Him.

35:40.169 --> 35:46.738
We often say, God, you know, I'll have my quiet time if I get absolutely everything else done today.

35:48.546 --> 35:51.790
And I happen to be left with two minutes at the end of the day.

35:51.870 --> 35:53.131
I'll give you those two minutes.

35:54.052 --> 35:59.899
That's the same thing as saying, God, I brought this blind lame cow to you for sacrifice.

36:01.421 --> 36:04.003
Now he is worth better than that.

36:05.325 --> 36:06.706
We offer him our careers.

36:07.347 --> 36:09.389
We don't selfishly seek our own fame.

36:10.411 --> 36:10.651
Right?

36:10.671 --> 36:12.353
We submit our jobs to him.

36:12.393 --> 36:15.556
We recognize that he is our ultimate boss.

36:15.917 --> 36:16.978
He is our Lord.

36:17.474 --> 36:19.397
that we answer to Him ultimately.

36:19.798 --> 36:33.864
And so whatever it is that you do for a living, whether it's being retired or, you know, and being able to serve other people and having time to be able to be involved in ministries, or whether you're still actively working, you are working for your boss.

36:33.944 --> 36:37.210
But as a Christian, you are ultimately working as unto the Lord.

36:37.650 --> 36:41.938
And so honor the Lord with everything that you do in your job.

36:43.362 --> 36:47.929
Treat people in your job the way that God wants you to treat people in your job.

36:49.091 --> 36:56.142
I want to ask the ushers to come forward and start to pass out the elements today for communion.

36:58.185 --> 37:02.652
Listen, whatever it is that God has called you to do, He calls people to be teachers.

37:02.712 --> 37:04.334
He calls people to be accountants.

37:04.354 --> 37:06.698
He calls people to be plumbers, electricians.

37:07.058 --> 37:11.986
He does not just call people to be pastors and missionaries.

37:12.194 --> 37:14.117
His call goes far beyond that.

37:14.578 --> 37:18.063
And so wherever it is that you find yourself, that is your mission field.

37:18.824 --> 37:26.056
You know, I used to have a guy that led music for a church one time when I was pastor in there and he owned some kind of a business.

37:26.116 --> 37:32.366
I can't remember what it was now, but he came in one day and he said, well, I have business Carl and then I have church Carl.

37:33.587 --> 37:36.772
And he said, I like to keep those two things separate.

37:38.315 --> 37:40.338
And I said, well, that's a huge mistake.

37:41.570 --> 37:44.974
You can't keep business Carl separate from church Carl.

37:46.275 --> 38:04.674
If you think that God cares, if you're ripping people off in your business and then you show up at church on Sunday and you put on church Carl and you think God is happy with you, then like George Strait said, I've got some oceanfront property in Arizona, I'd like to sell ya.

38:07.336 --> 38:08.818
It's not the way it works.

38:09.986 --> 38:13.190
The gospel permeates all of our lives.

38:13.911 --> 38:17.276
It permeates every single relationship.

38:18.978 --> 38:20.460
And finally, our money.

38:21.121 --> 38:22.703
God doesn't need our money, right?

38:22.743 --> 38:23.964
He is not impoverished.

38:24.986 --> 38:28.330
However, God does know that our money is tied to our hearts.

38:30.232 --> 38:37.522
And therefore, we can be generous with other people in need, that we're not supposed to be cheap or stingy.

38:38.850 --> 38:54.452
that in response to this glorious salvation that God has for us, that we are to offer a whole lives to him in worship and to bring him honor and glory and majesty that only he is due.

38:54.512 --> 39:04.146
And so for a moment, I want you to just pause and evaluate your life and say, you know, God, I love you.

39:05.570 --> 39:14.906
Think of the ways that God has blessed you as we enter into this time of communion and we celebrate the death and the resurrection of Jesus and the new life that's available.

39:15.386 --> 39:24.722
Take one moment and just think about how God has loved you and take one moment to examine yourself in saying, have I given God my best?

